{"author":{"id":"1260ec7e1e5fa2a41651bb0f92ca6302285a1546d07f404ff26b865b47ab5c24"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1660937961,"nonce":"OcirnRruJGwwgYZd+Yn9ti/Uzn0=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc5Ix4Ph","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/935#issuecomment-1221034977"},"message":"https://dandiarchive.org/server-info/ has \n```\n    \"cli-minimal-version\": \"0.14.2\",\n    \"cli-bad-versions\": []\n```\nso at least that version is required and no bad versions are listed - those fields are checked by `dandi-cli` [here](https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/blob/HEAD/dandi/utils.py#L594). Those are enforced for a specific server (of which we have only two - main and staging - ATM) while interacting with it (so for `upload`). `etelemetry` checks for new versions etc upon start of dandi-cli [here](https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/blob/HEAD/dandi/utils.py#L727).  So if we want to really force new dandi-cli versions to interact with our server, best is to adjust aforementioned cli-minimal-version.","files":null}]}